ESA-CCI soilmoisture Testcase

This test-case demonstrates reading the PASSIVE sensor type of the ESA-CCI soilmoisture datasets using EnKF-based assimilation into the NoahMP 4.0.1 LSM (over the Western U.S.).

It uses:
  (a) The MERRA2 and GPM IMERG forcing datasets
  (b) retrospective running mode
  (c) The NoahMP version 4.0.1 land surface model
  (d) Regional domain over the western US at 1 km spatial resolution
      (see the ldt.config file)
  (e) A time period from 23:30Z 30 Sep 2017 to 00Z 01 Nov 2017

This directory contains:
  (a) This README file
  (b) The "lis.config" file used for this testcase
  (c) The "MODEL_OUTPUT_LIST.TBL" file used by the lis.config file
      to select the output variables
  (d) An "output.ctl" file used to display the output in GrADS from
      the LIS run
  (e) The "ldt.config" file used to preprocess the domain and parameters
  (f) The "lvt.config" file used to postprocess the output

Note that the "lis.config" file should be edited
to make sure that the locations of the parameter and forcing files
are specified correctly.

To run this testcase:
  (a) Run the LIS executable using the "lis.config" file with the
      testcase input data.
